msgstr "warning\\ **Warning** Only ``GET`` endpoints are cached."

#: ../../source/techniques/caching.rst:55
msgid "Global cache"
msgstr "Global cache"

#: ../../source/techniques/caching.rst:57
msgid ""
"To reduce an amount of the required boilerplate, you can bind "
"``CacheInterceptor`` to each existing endpoint at once."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/techniques/caching.rst:79
msgid "WebSockets & Microservices"
msgstr "WebSockets & Microservices"

#: ../../source/techniques/caching.rst:81
msgid ""
"Obviously, you can effortlessly apply ``CacheInterceptor`` to WebSocket "
"subscribers as well as Microservice’s patterns (regardless of transport "
"method that is being used)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/techniques/caching.rst:104
msgid ""
"info **Hint** The ``@CacheKey()`` decorator is imported from "
"``@nestjs/common`` package."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/techniques/caching.rst:107
msgid ""
"However, the additional ``@CacheKey()`` decorator is required in order to"
" specify a key used to subsequently store and retrieve cached data. "
"Besides, please note that you **shouldn’t cache everything**. Actions "
"which responsibility is to perform some business operations rather than "
"simply querying the data should never be cached."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/techniques/caching.rst:114
msgid "Customize caching"
msgstr "Customize caching"

#: ../../source/techniques/caching.rst:116
msgid ""
"All cached data have its own expiration time (TTL). To customize default "
"values, pass options object to the ``register()`` method."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/techniques/caching.rst:127
msgid "Different stores"
msgstr "Different stores"

#: ../../source/techniques/caching.rst:129
msgid ""
"We take advantage of `cache-manager <https://github.com/BryanDonovan"
"/node-cache-manager>`__ under the hood. This package supports a wide-"
"range of useful stores, for example, `Redis <https://github.com/dabroek"
"/node-cache-manager-redis-store>`__ store (full list `here "
"<https://github.com/BryanDonovan/node-cache-manager#store-engines>`__). "
"To set up the Redis store, simple pass the package together with "
"corresponding options to the ``register()`` method."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/techniques/caching.rst:158
msgid "Adjust tracking"
msgstr "Adjust tracking"

#: ../../source/techniques/caching.rst:160
msgid ""
"By default, Nest uses request URL (in HTTP app) or cache key (in "
"websockets and microservices) set through ``@CacheKey()`` decorator to "
"associate cache records with your endpoints. Nevertheless, sometimes you "
"might want to set up tracking based on different factors, for example, "
"using HTTP headers (e.g. ``Authorization`` to properly identify "
"``profile`` endpoints)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/techniques/caching.rst:167
msgid ""
"In order to accomplish that, create a subclass of ``CacheInterceptor`` "
"and override ``trackBy()`` method."
msgstr ""

