msgid "And ``FindOneParams`` looks like below."
msgstr "And ``FindOneParams`` looks like below."

#: ../../source/techniques/validation.rst:103
msgid "Disable detailed errors"
msgstr "Disable detailed errors"

#: ../../source/techniques/validation.rst:105
msgid ""
"Error messages help a lot in order to comprehend what was wrong with the "
"data sent through the network. However, in some production environments, "
"you might want to disable detailed errors."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/techniques/validation.rst:117
msgid "Now, error messages won’t be populated to the end user."
msgstr "Now, error messages won’t be populated to the end user."

#: ../../source/techniques/validation.rst:120
msgid "Stripping properties"
msgstr "Stripping properties"

#: ../../source/techniques/validation.rst:122
msgid ""
"Quite frequently, we would like only predefined (whitelisted) properties "
"to be passed on. For instance, if we expect ``email`` and ``password`` "
"properties, when someone sends ``age``, this property should be stripped "
"and not available in the DTO. To enable such behavior, set ``whitelist`` "
"to ``true``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/techniques/validation.rst:136
msgid ""
"This setting will enable auto-stripping of non-whitelisted (without any "
"decorator on top of them) properties. However, if you want to stop the "
"request processing entirely, and return an error response to the user, "
"use ``forbidNonWhitelisted`` instead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/techniques/validation.rst:142
msgid "Auto payload transforming"
msgstr "Auto payload transforming"

#: ../../source/techniques/validation.rst:144
msgid ""
"The ``ValidationPipe`` doesn’t automatically transform your payloads to "
"the corresponding DTO classes. If you take a look at either "
"``createUserDto`` or ``findOneParams`` in your controller methods, you "
"will notice that they’re not actual instances of these classes. To enable"
" auto-transformation, set ``transform`` to ``true``."
msgstr ""

